column3: Banks head lower following rate hike
column4: The major averages, bonds, and gold have all turned higher after the Fed lifted the Fed Funds rate by 25 basis points, but satiated bank bulls might be lightening up just a hair.

For now, Washington D.C. is winning the battle against those in favor of quickly rolling back swaths of Dodd-Frank. For now, the Senate Banking Committee and House Financial Services Committee are working on other things, while Republicans instead spend political capital on things like Obamacare repeal and tax reform.

column3: Another big day for financials on tap after ADP number
column4: The ADP reported a whopping 298K jobs added in February, the third-best print of the recovery.
